{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-aaa62533438ffa17", "type": "tool_result", "content": "---EXIT --\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 41501 Jul 24 06:18 /tmp/paper_2607_21075.html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head><script>document.documentElement.classList.add('js');</script>  <title>[2607.21075v1] VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report</title>\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Abstract page for arXiv paper 2607.21075v1: VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\"><meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"website\" />\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\" />\n<meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\"/>\n  <script src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/cite.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script><meta name=\"citation_title\" content=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Xu, Songchen\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Song, Ting\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Huang, Shaohan\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Peng, Zhiliang\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Xia, Yan\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Tu, Yujie\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Huang, Xin\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Yu, Jianwei\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Dong, Li\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Wei, Furu\" /><meta name=\"citation_date\" content=\"2026/07/23\" /><meta name=\"citation_online_date\" content=\"2026/07/23\" /><meta name=\"citation_pdf_url\" content=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.21075\" /><meta name=\"citation_arxiv_id\" content=\"2607.21075\" /><meta name=\"citation_abstract\" content=\"We present VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet, a compressed variant of VibeVoice-ASR optimized for real-time inference on edge CPUs. We apply heterogeneous quantization tailored to the computational characteristics of each stage: the VAE acoustic tokenizer uses full-pipeline INT8 quantization (I8_S) with kernel fusion and SIMD optimization, while the autoregressive language model adopts BitNet-style ternary weights (I2_S). To preserve accuracy under aggressive compression, we employ a progressive quantization-aware training strategy. For inference, we implement custom SIMD kernels and fused operators within the ggml framework targeting both ARM and x86 platforms, achieving real-time recognition with RTF &lt; 1 using as few as 3 CPU threads. VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet is 1.6-2.3x faster than Whisper.cpp at comparable model sizes (~1.6 GB), with only modest accuracy degradation compared to the FP16 baseline.\" />\n    <a href=\"https://info.arxiv.org/about/donate.html\">Donate</a>\n        placeholder=\"Search papers by title, author, abstract, or ID...\">\n        dc:title=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\"\n    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report</h1>\n    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Xu,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Songchen Xu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Song,+T\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ting Song</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Huang,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Shaohan Huang</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Peng,+Z\" rel=\"nofollow\">Zhiliang Peng</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Xia,+Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yan Xia</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Tu,+Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yujie Tu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Huang,+X\" rel=\"nofollow\">Xin Huang</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Yu,+J\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jianwei Yu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Dong,+L\" rel=\"nofollow\">Li Dong</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Wei,+F\" rel=\"nofollow\">Furu Wei</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report, by Songchen Xu and 9 other authors</div>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"/pdf/2607.21075v1\">View PDF</a>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.21075v1\">HTML (experimental)</a>\n    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>We present VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet, a compressed variant of VibeVoice-ASR optimized for real-time inference on edge CPUs. We apply heterogeneous quantization tailored to the computational characteristics of each stage: the VAE acoustic tokenizer uses full-pipeline INT8 quantization (I8_S) with kernel fusion and SIMD optimization, while the autoregressive language model adopts BitNet-style ternary weights (I2_S). To preserve accuracy under aggressive compression, we employ a progressive quantization-aware training strategy. For inference, we implement custom SIMD kernels and fused operators within the ggml framework targeting both ARM and x86 platforms, achieving real-time recognition with RTF &lt; 1 using as few as 3 CPU threads. VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet is 1.6-2.3x faster than <a href=\"http://Whisper.cpp\" rel=\"external noopener nofollow\" class=\"link-external link-http\">this http URL</a> at comparable model sizes (~1.6 GB), with only modest accuracy degradation compared to the FP16 baseline.\nView a PDF of the paper titled VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report, by Songchen Xu and 9 other authors</div><li><a href=\"/pdf/2607.21075v1\" aria-describedby=\"download-button-info\" accesskey=\"f\" class=\"abs-button download-pdf\">View PDF</a></li><li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.21075v1\" class=\"abs-button\" id=\"latexml-download-link\">HTML (experimental)</a></li><li><a href=\"/src/2607.21075v1\" class=\"abs-button download-eprint\">TeX Source\n      <div class=\"abs-license\"><a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\" title=\"Rights to this article\" class=\"has_license\">\n         accesskey=\"p\" title=\"previous in cs.SD (accesskey p)\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&nbsp;prev</a>\n         title=\"next in cs.SD (accesskey n)\"  rel=\"nofollow\">next&nbsp;&gt;</a>", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "fe9c1bc6-5ae7-48ce-99f1-21f722918975", "uuid": "183482fb-38ad-4a52-8644-5cf6979eb4ce", "timestamp": "2026-07-24T06:18:42.392Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "---EXIT --\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 41501 Jul 24 06:18 /tmp/paper_2607_21075.html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head><script>document.documentElement.classList.add('js');</script>  <title>[2607.21075v1] VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report</title>\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Abstract page for arXiv paper 2607.21075v1: VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\"><meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"website\" />\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\" />\n<meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\"/>\n  <script src=\"/static/browse/0.3.4/js/cite.js\" type=\"text/javascript\"></script><meta name=\"citation_title\" content=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Xu, Songchen\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Song, Ting\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Huang, Shaohan\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Peng, Zhiliang\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Xia, Yan\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Tu, Yujie\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Huang, Xin\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Yu, Jianwei\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Dong, Li\" /><meta name=\"citation_author\" content=\"Wei, Furu\" /><meta name=\"citation_date\" content=\"2026/07/23\" /><meta name=\"citation_online_date\" content=\"2026/07/23\" /><meta name=\"citation_pdf_url\" content=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2607.21075\" /><meta name=\"citation_arxiv_id\" content=\"2607.21075\" /><meta name=\"citation_abstract\" content=\"We present VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet, a compressed variant of VibeVoice-ASR optimized for real-time inference on edge CPUs. We apply heterogeneous quantization tailored to the computational characteristics of each stage: the VAE acoustic tokenizer uses full-pipeline INT8 quantization (I8_S) with kernel fusion and SIMD optimization, while the autoregressive language model adopts BitNet-style ternary weights (I2_S). To preserve accuracy under aggressive compression, we employ a progressive quantization-aware training strategy. For inference, we implement custom SIMD kernels and fused operators within the ggml framework targeting both ARM and x86 platforms, achieving real-time recognition with RTF &lt; 1 using as few as 3 CPU threads. VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet is 1.6-2.3x faster than Whisper.cpp at comparable model sizes (~1.6 GB), with only modest accuracy degradation compared to the FP16 baseline.\" />\n    <a href=\"https://info.arxiv.org/about/donate.html\">Donate</a>\n        placeholder=\"Search papers by title, author, abstract, or ID...\">\n        dc:title=\"VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report\"\n    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report</h1>\n    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Xu,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Songchen Xu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Song,+T\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ting Song</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Huang,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Shaohan Huang</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Peng,+Z\" rel=\"nofollow\">Zhiliang Peng</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Xia,+Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yan Xia</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Tu,+Y\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yujie Tu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Huang,+X\" rel=\"nofollow\">Xin Huang</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Yu,+J\" rel=\"nofollow\">Jianwei Yu</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Dong,+L\" rel=\"nofollow\">Li Dong</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Wei,+F\" rel=\"nofollow\">Furu Wei</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report, by Songchen Xu and 9 other authors</div>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"/pdf/2607.21075v1\">View PDF</a>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.21075v1\">HTML (experimental)</a>\n    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>We present VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet, a compressed variant of VibeVoice-ASR optimized for real-time inference on edge CPUs. We apply heterogeneous quantization tailored to the computational characteristics of each stage: the VAE acoustic tokenizer uses full-pipeline INT8 quantization (I8_S) with kernel fusion and SIMD optimization, while the autoregressive language model adopts BitNet-style ternary weights (I2_S). To preserve accuracy under aggressive compression, we employ a progressive quantization-aware training strategy. For inference, we implement custom SIMD kernels and fused operators within the ggml framework targeting both ARM and x86 platforms, achieving real-time recognition with RTF &lt; 1 using as few as 3 CPU threads. VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet is 1.6-2.3x faster than <a href=\"http://Whisper.cpp\" rel=\"external noopener nofollow\" class=\"link-external link-http\">this http URL</a> at comparable model sizes (~1.6 GB), with only modest accuracy degradation compared to the FP16 baseline.\nView a PDF of the paper titled VibeVoice-ASR-BitNet Technical Report, by Songchen Xu and 9 other authors</div><li><a href=\"/pdf/2607.21075v1\" aria-describedby=\"download-button-info\" accesskey=\"f\" class=\"abs-button download-pdf\">View PDF</a></li><li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.21075v1\" class=\"abs-button\" id=\"latexml-download-link\">HTML (experimental)</a></li><li><a href=\"/src/2607.21075v1\" class=\"abs-button download-eprint\">TeX Source\n      <div class=\"abs-license\"><a href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\" title=\"Rights to this article\" class=\"has_license\">\n         accesskey=\"p\" title=\"previous in cs.SD (accesskey p)\" rel=\"nofollow\">&lt;&nbsp;prev</a>\n         title=\"next in cs.SD (accesskey n)\"  rel=\"nofollow\">next&nbsp;&gt;</a>", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
